hin the wide range of objectives set in education in this country, the government should strive to provide an effective system and accordingly provide appropriate resources. 
\par <#/>If the government cannot afford, then measures must be improvised as the economy has a lot of philanthropists at this material time. <#/>We should take advantage of the moment when education is viewed as crucial for development. 
